snippet: Rooney’s goal, which tied Bobby Charlton’s total of 49 for the national team, paced a rout of a San Marino team made up of part-time players.
abstract: England defeats Spain, 6-0, to become first team qualifying for 2016 European Championship; Spain beat Slovakia, 2-0; other soccer news noted.
lead_paragraph: Rooney’s goal, which tied Bobby Charlton’s total of 49 for the national team, paced a rout of a San Marino team made up of part-time players.

headline.main: England Qualifies, and Wayne Rooney Ties Record
headline.print_headline: England Qualifies; Spain Avenges a Loss
